      • sortNamesAccordingToIndex

        public static List<String> sortNamesAccordingToIndex(List<String> names,
                                                     int[] indices)
                                              throws IllegalArgumentException
        Sorts the names according to the indices ascending order.
        Parameters:
        names - Some Strings.
        indices - The (unique!) indices.
        Returns:
        The names ordered by indices, if there are less indices, the rest of the names are copied to the end.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - There were duplicate values in indices.
